The paper deals with channel estimation and capacity analysis in a massive MU-MIMO downlink system, which involves information theory (cs.IT), networking and communications (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), and multimedia (cs.MM). The use of linear precoding and downlink pilots also suggests the possibility of the paper being categorized under computer networks and communications (cs.COM).
